  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Schizophrenia is a severe mental illness which is considered to have, among other, a genetic
      etiology. One of the most efficient tools in genetic-psychiatry is the investigation of
      multiplex families.

      The current study will identify patients of multiplex families and to map their family
      connections and the presence of mental illnesses among family members.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
